<item>
            <title>[LU-8903] Drop &quot;Segmentation fault and Bus error messages&quot; in the calling shell for racer tests</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8903</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As per Andreas proposal:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; it would be possible to filter out only the Segmentation fault and Bus error messages in the calling shell:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;while /bin/true ; do&lt;br/&gt;
    file=$((RANDOM % MAX))&lt;br/&gt;
    cp $PROG $DIR/$file &amp;gt; /dev/null 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;1&lt;br/&gt;
    $DIR/$file 0.$((RANDOM % 5 + 1)) 2&amp;gt; /dev/null&lt;br/&gt;
    sleep $((RANDOM % 3))&lt;br/&gt;
done 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;1 | egrep -v &quot;Segmentation fault|Bus error&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; though it may also be necessary to &quot;export LANG=C&quot; so that the messages are in English instead of the local language. Easier to just drop all error messages, like the other scripts do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
